{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"stun-wraith-conch","description":"## Why\nClaiming with no `--assignee` (or with a non-Jira handle) leaves tickets effectively unassigned â€” and a bare handle like `joe` gets cleared by Jira sync (see bug `balm-feast-mica`). A configurable default assignee lets a checkout/agent set a sensible Jira-resolvable identity once, so claims attribute work correctly by default.\n\n## What\nAdd a `default_assignee` config key (config file + env override, following the existing rebar config pattern), and make `claim` fall back to it when `--assignee` is unspecified/empty.\n\n## Scope\n**Config** (`src/rebar/config.py`):\n- Add `default_assignee: str = \"\"` to the existing `TicketConfig` dataclass (the `[tickets]` section) â€” it is a ticket-workflow setting, not a Jira-connector setting.\n- Wire the env override following the established pattern: either the auto-derived `REBAR_TICKET_DEFAULT_ASSIGNEE`, or add an explicit entry to `_CANONICAL_ENV_NAMES` if a nicer name is wanted. Precedence stays CLI > env > project config > user config > default.\n- Register the key in `_SECTIONS` so typo-detection (`unknown key â€¦ ignored`) and `env_overrides()` pick it up.\n\n**Claim** (`src/rebar/_commands/claim.py`):\n- In `claim_compute()`, BEFORE `txn.claim_core(...)` (~line 140), if `assignee` is empty, fall back to `config.load_config(repo_root).ticket.default_assignee`.\n- The existing `claim_core` (`txn.py`) already writes the assignee as an EDIT event only when non-empty â€” unchanged.\n- Behavior: explicit `--assignee` always wins; empty + configured default â†’ default is used; empty + no default â†’ unchanged (no assignee), as today.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `[tickets] default_assignee = \"<id>\"` in the config file is read and applied.\n- [ ] Env override (`REBAR_TICKET_DEFAULT_ASSIGNEE` or the chosen canonical name) overrides the file value; precedence CLI > env > project > user > default holds.\n- [ ] `claim <id>` with no `--assignee` uses the configured default; `claim <id> --assignee X` still uses X (explicit wins); empty + no default behaves exactly as today.\n- [ ] The key is in the known-key set (no \"unknown key\" warning) and documented in `docs/config.md`.\n- [ ] Recommend (doc note) that the default be a Jira-resolvable identity (email/accountId) so it survives reconcile â€” ties to bug `balm-feast-mica`.\n- [ ] Tests: config load (file + env + precedence), and claim fallback (explicit / default / none) including the cascade claim path.\n\n## Affected Files (initial)\n- `src/rebar/config.py` (`TicketConfig`, `_SECTIONS`, `_CANONICAL_ENV_NAMES`)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/claim.py` (`claim_compute` fallback)\n- `docs/config.md`","id":"c36c-357a-2900-4ed7","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Add default_assignee config (file + env override) and have claim use it when --assignee is omitted"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782753339024268001,"uuid":"6cebf5e4-2b0a-4e9b-87c2-a965a5df70ff"}